<h4>Answers</h4>
<ul class="faq">
	<li>
		<a name="ticket-sale"></a>
		<h5>When do tickets go on sale?</h5>
		<p>Tickets go on sale to King&rsquo;s Members at <strong>12:00pm Monday 6<sup>th</sup> February</strong> till <strong>12:00pm Friday 10<sup>th</sup> February</strong>.</p>
		<p>Tickets go on sale to the rest of the University at <strong>12:00pm Friday 10<sup>th</sup> February</strong>.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="ticket-price"></a>
		<h5>How much are the tickets?</h5>
		<p>Tickets for King&rsquo; Members are <strong>&pound;70</strong>.</p>
		<p>University Members&rsquo; and all guests&rsquo; (including those of King&rsquo; Members) tickets are <strong>&pound;85</strong>.</p>
		<p>QueueJump tickets will cost an extra <strong>&pound;10</strong> on top of the standard ticket prices.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="theme"></a>
		<h5>What is the theme this year?</h5>
		<p>The theme this year is Uncanny Valley.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="queuejump"></a>
		<h5>What is QueueJump?</h5>
		<p>QueueJump tickets will allow you to enter the King&rsquo;s Affair earlier than Normal tickets and will cost an extra <strong>&pound;10</strong>.</p>
		<p>This means less time spent waiting in the 1400 person queue and first access to food, drink and ents.</p>
		<p>King&rsquo;s members + Q-jump - &pound;80<br/>Non-King&rsquo;s members + Q-jump - &pound;95</p>

	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="guests"></a>
		<h5>Can I purchase guest tickets after I confirmed my order?</h5>
		<p>No you may not add additional guest tickets after you have confirmed your order.</p>
		<p>Please make sure that you do this before you confirm your order</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="names"></a>
		<h5>Can I change names on my tickets?</h5>
		<p>You may change names on tickets until 9pm on Saturday 1<sup>st</sup> April for <strong>&pound;10</strong> per name change.</p>
			                       <p>Name changes will cost <strong>&pound;20</strong> per name change from then until 9pm on Monday 1<sup>st</sup> May.</p>
					                       <p>Thereafter name changes will cost <strong>&pound;30</strong> per name change and can be made up until 11pm on Monday 19<sup>th</sup> June.</p>

		<p>Name changes are not possible for principal tickets, except in exceptional circumstances at the discretion of the Chair and the ticketing officer.</p>
		<p>Changes will not be reflected on actual tickets but on our electronic records.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="cheques"></a>
		<h5>What are the Bank Transfer details?</h5>
		<p>Details for Bank Transfers will be available to you when you log on to the website and in the Confirmation Email sent to you.</p>
		<p>If you have any issues finding details, please contact the <a href="mailto:webmaster@kingsaffair.com">webmaster</a>.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="problem"></a>
		<h5>I have a problem with my order, what should I do?</h5>
		<p>Don&rsquo;t worry! Just send an email to <a href="mailto:ticketing@kingsaffair.com">ticketing@kingsaffair.com</a> describing the issue and we will sort it out for you.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="alumni"></a>
		<h5>How can King's alumni get tickets?</h5>
		<p>King's alumni are entitled to one ticket at the King's alumni price of &pound;85.</p>
		<p>To order your ticket please contact <a href="mailto:ticketing@kingsaffair.com">ticketing</a> before the end of King's ticket release window.</p>
		<p>Please note alumni status will be checked by college.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<a name="pickup"></a>
		<h5>When is ticket collection?</h5>
		<p>You may collect your tickets from the bar in King's. Times will be announced in due course, primarily via the Facebook page so please keep an eye out for it there.</p>
		<p>Only the primary ticket holder will be allowed to collect the tickets unless notice is given beforehand.</p>
		<p>You must bring a University Card or Photo ID when you collect your tickets.</p>
		<p>Failure to collect tickets by Monday 19th of June will result in a £10 fine.</p>
	</li>
</ul>
